All Implemented Interfaces:
IDocumentPane, ComponentListener, ContainerListener, ImageObserver, MenuContainer, PropertyChangeListener, Serializable, EventListener, Accessible, ChangeListener, SwingConstants
public class CodeEditorDocumentPane
extends DocumentPane

CodeEditorDocumentPane is a special DocumentPane for CodeEditors. The only difference between this and the DocuemntPane is this one changes the "New Horizontal Group" and "New Vertical Group" context menu items to "SplitHorizontallyy" and "Split Vertically" respectively. If you use CodeEditorDocumentComponent as the DocumentComponent, it will split the CodeEditor into two CodeEditors which are editing the same content.
